    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @ledbetterljoshua \r\n\r\nThe `searchParameters` prop is now deprecated. You can use the `Configure` widget to apply any `searchParameters`. See: https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/guide/Search_parameters.html\r\n\r\nThen, you can use the `filters` search parameter which as an easier syntax than `facetFilters`.\r\nSee: https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-client/javascript/parameters/filters/\r\n\r\nIt would mean having something like this: \r\n\r\n    <Configure\r\n             filters=\"publishDate <= timestamp\"\r\n             hitsPerPage = {3}\r\n    />\r\n",
